OL,3,CTim Davie and Deborah Turness'
OL,4,Cresignation statements in full
OL,6,FIn these increasingly polarised times,
OL,7,Fthe BBC is of unique value and speaks
OL,8,Fto the very best of us. It helps make
OL,9,Fthe UK a special place; overwhelmingly
OL,10,Fkind, tolerant and curious. Like all
OL,11,Fpublic organisations, the BBC is not
OL,12,Fperfect, and we must always be open,
OL,13,Ftransparent and accountable. While not
OL,14,Fbeing the only reason, the current
OL,15,Fdebate around BBC News has
OL,16,Funderstandably contributed to my
OL,17,Fdecision. Overall the BBC is
OL,18,Fdelivering well, but there have been
OL,19,Fsome mistakes made and as Director-
OL,20,FGeneral I have to take ultimate
OL,21,Fresponsibility.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
