OL,3,CTim Davie and Deborah Turness'
OL,4,Cresignation statements in full
OL,6,FThis timing allows a new DG to help
OL,7,Fshape the next Charter. I believe we
OL,8,Fare in a strong position to deliver
OL,9,Fgrowth.
OL,11,FThank you again, it has been a
OL,12,Fwonderful ride, which I have loved. I
OL,13,Fcount myself very lucky to have served
OL,14,Fas DG no.17. I will have a proper
OL,15,Fchance to see many of you before I go
OL,16,Fbut I have been incredibly proud to
OL,17,Flead the BBC as DG for over five
OL,18,Fyears. It is a precious UK institution
OL,19,Fand you are a world-class team. Thank
OL,20,Fyou all for the tireless support and
OL,21,Ffriendship.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/15
